data.name: numericUpDownTempMin.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum GPU temperature or memory junction temperature. The temperature measured depends on the respective metric query you've selected in the Data Tracking grid. Unit (i.e. Celsius, Fahrenheit) is determined by the Hardware Monitor app. If temp goes below this value, MineControl will try to increase GPU power step.

data.name: numericUpDownTempMax.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum GPU temperature or memory junction temperature. The temperature measured depends on the respective metric query you've selected in the Data Tracking grid. Unit (i.e. Celsius, Fahrenheit) is determined by the Hardware Monitor app. If temp goes above this value, MineControl will try to decrease GPU power step.

data.value: When enabled, entire MineControl config will be archived when changed. Evaluated on the archive interval and when closing MineControl. Note: Fluctuating settings like GPU power step don't trigger config archiving.

data.name: numericUpDownTempGPUShutOffThresholdSecs.ToolTip
data.value: When enabled and GPU power step is at the minimum, MineControl will stop the GPU miner for the specified number of seconds when max temp is exceeded for the specified number of seconds. This happens regardless of other settings, like post-step wait. For example, if set to 60/30, GPU miner is stopped for 60 seconds when max memory junction temp is exceeded on each polling interval for 30 seconds. Warning: Conditions are only checked on the polling interval!
